article.headline: UC Irvine 65, Cal St.-Fullerton 62
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Eric Wise scored 20 points and Brett Lauer made two free throws with 7.1 seconds left to give UC Irvine a 65-62 victory over Cal State Fullerton on Saturday night. Michael Hunter added 16 points, Kevin Bland had 12 rebounds and four blocks and Patrick Rembert passed for a career-high nine assists for the Anteaters (12-18, 8-8 Big West), who won four of their past five. Aaron Thompson tied his career best with 19 points for the Titans (14-16, 7-9), who have lost six of eight. Josh Akognon and Jacques Streeter scored 13 points apiece.
